      <h2 class="section-title">What is a <em>55+ community</em>?</h2>
      <div class="section-rule"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="what-intro-col">
      <div>
        <p>A 55+ community — also known as an active adult community — is a residential development legally designated under the Housing for Older Persons Act (HOPA) for residents aged 55 and older. At least 80% of occupied homes must have one resident who meets that age requirement.</p>
        <p>But the number is the least interesting thing about them. These communities are designed around a specific way of living: less maintenance, more connection, more time for the things that actually matter to you — whether that's golf, travel, gardening, creative hobbies, or simply a peaceful place to call home.</p>
        <p>From cozy townhome villages to resort-style master-planned developments with every imaginable amenity, 55+ communities vary enormously — and finding the right fit takes local knowledge and honest guidance. That's exactly what Gabriela provides.</p>
        <br/>
        <button class="btn-sky" onclick="showPage('why')">Discover if it's right for you →</button>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="what-photo" style="background:url('https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1564013799919-ab600027ffc6?w=900&q=80') center/cover no-repeat" role="img" aria-label="55+ active adult community in Palm Desert, Southern California">
          <div class="what-photo-caption">Resort-style 55+ community, Palm Desert, CA</div>
        </div>
        <p class="photo-location">📍 Coachella Valley, Southern California</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="what-grid">
      <div class="what-card">
        <div style="height:160px;background:url('https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1572120360610-d971b9d7767c?w=600&q=80') center/cover no-repeat;margin:-44px -40px 20px;position:relative">
          <div style="position:absolute;bottom:0;left:0;right:0;background:rgba(92,61,30,0.55);padding:6px 12px">
