    </div>
    <div class="page-hero-sub-content">
      <h1>Why choose a 55+ community?</h1>
      <p>The honest case for a new chapter — what these communities offer, who they're really for, and how to know if it's your right move.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="why-section">
    <div style="max-width:1100px">
      <div style="margin-bottom:56px">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">Six Reasons People Choose 55+</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">It's not about <em>slowing down</em>.</h2>
        <div class="section-rule"></div>
        <p style="margin-top:20px;max-width:640px;font-size:0.95rem;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.85">The most common thing Gabriela hears from clients after they've moved into a 55+ community: "I wish I'd done this sooner." Here's why they say it.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-reasons">
        <div class="why-card">
          <div class="why-number">1</div>
          <h3>More time. Immediately.</h3>
          <p>When the HOA covers landscaping, exterior maintenance, and common areas, the weekend opens up in ways that surprise people. Suddenly there's time for the things you said you'd do "someday."</p>
        </div>
        <div class="why-card">
          <div class="why-number">2</div>
          <h3>Neighbors who get it.</h3>
          <p>Living among people at a similar stage of life means shared interests, natural conversation, and genuine friendships that form faster than in mixed-age neighborhoods. Loneliness — a real health concern — diminishes significantly in active adult communities.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="why-card">
          <div class="why-number">3</div>
          <h3>Amenities at your front door.</h3>
          <p>Pools, fitness centers, clubs, classes, pickleball courts, community gardens, art studios. These aren't extras — they're the point. For many, the activity calendar alone changes their daily life in profound ways.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="why-card">
          <div class="why-number">4</div>
          <h3>Security and peace of mind.</h3>
          <p>Many 55+ communities are gated, with active security, neighborhood watch programs, and a level of shared investment in the community's wellbeing that goes beyond what most standard neighborhoods offer.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="why-card">
          <div class="why-number">5</div>
          <h3>Homes designed for how you live now.</h3>
          <p>Single-story layouts, wider doorways, no-step entries, accessible bathrooms, and thoughtful floor plans are built-in — not retrofitted. The home works for you, not the other way around.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="why-card">
          <div class="why-number">6</div>
          <h3>A sound financial decision.</h3>
          <p>55+ communities tend to hold their value well. Residents are invested in keeping the community attractive. HOA funds maintain property values. And the predictability of what your home demands — financially and physically — reduces stress significantly in retirement.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="why-cta-block">
    <h2>Let's find yours.</h2>
    <p>Gabriela has toured communities throughout California — and she'll tell you honestly which ones are worth your time and which ones aren't.</p>
